-- Toyota Says Seven Lexus Models May Have Problem Causing Engines to Stall
-- Takako Iwatani
-- 2010-07-01T02:47:16Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/toyota-says-seven-lexus-models-may-have-engine-stall-defect-considers-fix.html

          
          
             Seven Toyota Motor Corp. Lexus-brand
models may have an engine-stall problem, spokeswoman Ririko
Takeuchi said by phone from Tokyo.  
 Toyota is considering its  next step to fix the problem,
which may also affect Toyota Crown models, she said. The stall
issue may affect 90,000 vehicles in Japan out of  a total of
270,000 worldwide.  
 To contact the reporter on this story:
Takako Iwatani in Tokyo at 
 tiwatani@bloomberg.net   
          
          


  
     
       
     
           
                            
                     
                     Toyota Motor Corp.'s 2010 Lexus LS460 luxury sport sedan is photographed during a media unveiling in San Diego. Photographer: Mark Elias/Bloomberg  
                           

     
